NAME
    gcloud alpha monitoring policies describe - describe an alerting policy

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha monitoring policies describe POLICY [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Describe an alerting policy.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     Policy resource - The alerting policy to describe. This represents a Cloud
     resource. (NOTE) Some attributes are not given arguments in this group but
     can be set in other ways. To set the [project] attribute: provide the flag
     [policy] on the command line with a fully specified name; provide the flag
     [--project] on the command line; set the property [core/project]. This
     must be specified.

       POLICY
          The ID of the policy or a fully qualified identifier for the policy.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

API REFERENCE
    This command uses the monitoring/v3 API. The full documentation for this
    API can be found at: https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/api/

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. If this
    command fails with API permission errors despite specifying the right
    project, you will have to apply for early access and have your projects
    registered on the API whitelist to use it. To do so, contact Support at
    https://cloud.google.com/support/.

